oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Lt. James Joseph Coghlan
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This head and upper body photograph is of Lt. Coghlan (Oct. 15, 1896-Sept. 3, 1963). The Still Image show a young man in uniform with the strap of his Sam Browne belt passing under the right shoulder strap of his uniform coat. Coglan served on the Mexican border in 1916, and in Preny (France) with the 3rd Batt., 55th Infantry.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Coghlan, James Joseph
